@kkseattle I’m not that speedy, it’s not in my nature. I tend to be more deliberative but probably lack the intellectual horsepower to complete any crossword in 6 minutes let alone a Saturday. I’m no brighter than I was 20 years ago but I’m much faster. This statistical case study of one identifies a correlation between speed and experience and none between speed and intelligence. 
I checked my August 16 time and see that it took me 1:03 compared to today’s 26 minutes. It’s been 1449 days since a puzzle defeated me and made me look something up. My times also vary as I might do other things while solving but my ritual is enjoy it at the beginning of my day. I find it interesting that my averages bear out the relative difficulty through the week like a flight of stairs and as I’ve gained experience those stairs have become less steep. 
I wouldn’t pay any attention to other people’s pace, just grind away at likely letter combinations when stuck until the thing unlocks.

