Speed-reading!  It's my contention that the only books that lend themselves to this "technique" are not actually worth reading (not even speedily!)  I recently encountered such a book--a sweet friend loved it and insisted that I accept the book as a loan.  Within the first few pages, I knew the book was a stinker--poor writing, predictable plotting, smarmy and sappy.  Out of loyalty I decided to try to get through it quickly, but it was incredibly frustrating--leaving me writhing, wincing, and dreading the next chapter as the plodding pace dragged on....   Oh, to be a speed-reader!!!  
