@Jane Wheelaghan

A cake donut is denser than most other types of donut like jelly donuts or crème-filled donuts. It’s more the consistency of a heavy cake, and more crumbly than the other kinds. The little donut pieces that Dunkin’ markets as Munchkins, and some others call “donut holes” are generally of the cake kind. Apple cider donuts, which will be ubiquitous any day now around here, are a type of cake donut. 

Of course, since the Brits call cookies biscuits, and biscuits scones (which they aren’t), who knows what kinds of donuts you have over there.

